\begin_layout Subsection
System Architecture
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:System-Architecture"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
OptimSolution is implemented in ISO C++17 and organised into two principal components:
 a platform-independent core library (optimcore) and a Qt6-based graphical front-end.
 The CLI executable links directly against optimcore and is built independently of the GUI,
 enabling headless execution on server environments.
 The build system is CMake (≥ 3.16),
 which manages both targets through a unified configuration.
 The core library is structured into four layers.
 The problem layer provides a catalogue of benchmark and real-world continuous optimization problems,
 currently comprising 92 instances.
 These include classical analytical functions among them Sphere,
 Rastrigin 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Mühlenbein"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Rosenbrock 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Rosenbrock"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Ackley 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Ackley"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Griewank,
 Levy,
 Schwefel,
 Michalewicz,
 Zakharov,
 Bohachevsky,
 Camel,
 Easom,
 Shubert,
 Hansen,
 Gallagher,
 and Weierstrass,
 documented in the comprehensive survey by Jamil and Yang 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Jamil"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 the full CEC 2022 benchmark suite 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Kumar"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 GKLS random function instances 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Gaviano"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 the complete CEC 2011 suite of real-world optimization problems 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Das"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 and additional engineering design problems covering antenna array synthesis,
 heat exchanger design,
 economic load dispatch,
 transmission network expansion planning,
 and kinematic inverse problems,
 among others.
 In its current version (v51),
 OptimSolution addresses unconstrained and bound-constrained continuous optimization problems exclusively,
 support for problems with nonlinear equality or inequality constraints is identified as a direction for future work (Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:conclusions"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

).
 The method layer currently includes 67 optimization algorithms.
 Population-based metaheuristics comprise Differential Evolution,
 Particle Swarm PSO,
 GA,
 Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy (CMA-ES) 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Hansen2"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Whale optimization Algorithm (WOA) 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Mirjalili"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Grey Wolf Optimiser (GWO) 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Mirjalili2"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Artificial Bee Colony (ABC) 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Karaboga"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Simulated Annealing (SA) 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Kirkpatrick"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 Ant Colony optimization for Continuous domains 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Socha"
literal "false"

\end_inset

