\begin_layout Standard
Method sensitivity analysis examines how variations in an algorithm's own hyper-parameters affect its performance on a selected set of problems.
 The user specifies the parameter of interest and the discrete values to evaluate through the Sensitivity panel of the Settings window,
 the framework then executes the method for each parameter value across all selected problems for the configured number of independent runs,
 and produces a Results table reporting for each parameter value the mean best objective value,
 standard deviation,
 minimum,
 maximum,
 main effect,
 rank,
 and number of runs.
